  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:Grit::Commit/2d7f0a46c3f58278f883cb829d9e8a109151559d</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/commit/2d7f0a46c3f58278f883cb829d9e8a109151559d"/>
    <title>
        Fix updating plugin options (#5144)
    </title>
    <updated>2018-01-13T13:23:50Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/3874900?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>simonbrunel</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/simonbrunel</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Fix updating plugin options (#5144)

Cached plugin descriptors hold a reference on the plugin options, which break if the plugin options object is replaced. That case happens when the user updates the plugin options with a new object, but also since the new config update logic (#4198) that now always clones the plugin options. The fix consists in explicitly invalidating that cache before updating the chart.&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
